#72: 
Subject: [PATCH] x86: attempt reboot via port CF9 if we have standard PCI ports

ERROR:GLOBAL_INITIALISERS: do not initialise globals to false
#128: FILE: arch/x86/kernel/reboot.c:40:
+bool port_cf9_safe = false;

Global variables should not be initialized explicitly to
0 (or NULL, false, etc.).  Your compiler (or rather your
loader, which is responsible for zeroing out the relevant
sections) automatically does it for you.

WARNING:PREFER_FALLTHROUGH: Prefer 'fallthrough;' over fallthrough comment
#186: FILE: arch/x86/kernel/reboot.c:414:
+			/* fall through */

Use the `fallthrough;` pseudo keyword instead of
`/* fallthrough */` like comments.

WARNING:LINE_SPACING: Missing a blank line after declarations
#191: FILE: arch/x86/kernel/reboot.c:419:
+				u8 cf9 = inb(0xcf9) & ~6;
+				outb(cf9|2, 0xcf9); /* Request hard reset */

Vertical space is wasted given the limited number of lines an
editor window can display when multiple blank lines are used.

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#spaces

CHECK:SPACING: spaces preferred around that '|' (ctx:VxV)
#191: FILE: arch/x86/kernel/reboot.c:419:
+				outb(cf9|2, 0xcf9); /* Request hard reset */
 				        ^

Whitespace style used in the kernel sources is described in kernel docs.

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#spaces

CHECK:USLEEP_RANGE: usleep_range is preferred over udelay; see Documentation/timers/timers-howto.rst
#192: FILE: arch/x86/kernel/reboot.c:420:
+				udelay(50);

usleep_range() should be preferred over udelay(). The proper way of
using usleep_range() is mentioned in the kernel docs.

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/timers/timers-howto.html#delays-information-on-the-various-kernel-delay-sleep-mechanisms

CHECK:SPACING: spaces preferred around that '|' (ctx:VxV)
#193: FILE: arch/x86/kernel/reboot.c:421:
+				outb(cf9|6, 0xcf9); /* Actually do the reset */
 				        ^

CHECK:USLEEP_RANGE: usleep_range is preferred over udelay; see Documentation/timers/timers-howto.rst
#194: FILE: arch/x86/kernel/reboot.c:422:
+				udelay(50);

WARNING:CONST_STRUCT: struct pci_raw_ops should normally be const
#208: FILE: arch/x86/pci/direct.c:176:
+struct pci_raw_ops pci_direct_conf2 = {

Using const is generally a good idea.  Checkpatch reads
a list of frequently used structs that are always or
almost always constant.

The existing structs list can be viewed from
`scripts/const_structs.checkpatch`.

See: https://lore.kernel.org/lkml/alpine.DEB.2.10.1608281509480.3321@hadrien/

